The Reflexion of this Originall Glory ſhining upon the duſt, the duſt became Light, that is man, for ſo the Antients termed him; 
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                   ſaith Phavorinus, we call a man light. but the opacous body of ſinne interpoſing it ſelfe betwixt this borrowed Light, and the Fountaine, caſt a ſhadow, the ſhadow of death.

